item.title: 阿根廷经济快照：央行美元购买狂潮放缓
item.description: 阿根廷央行已开始为积极购买美元踩刹车，这是在新任自由派总统哈维尔-米莱（Javier Milei）领导下建立储备的关键举措，分析人士认为这与当地农民谷物销售低于预期有关。【原文：Argentina's central bank has started to put the brakes on its aggressive buying of dollars, a key push to build up reserves under new libertarian President Javier Milei, something analysts pegged to weaker-than-expected sales of grains by local farmers.】

item.title: 空中客车公司寻求强制周末加班，以赶上延迟的 A220 生产
item.description: 三位熟知内情的消息人士告诉路透社，空中客车公司已告知蒙特利尔地区 A220 工厂的工人，该公司希望在周末强制加班，以赶上亏损喷气机的延迟生产。【原文：Airbus has told workers at its Montreal-area A220 factory that it wants to impose mandatory overtime on weekends to catch up on delayed production of the money-losing jet, three sources familiar with the matter told Reuters.】

item.title: 美国 这波反弹能否对抗美联储？
item.description: 市场通讯员 Naomi Rovnick 对美国和全球市场未来一天的展望【原文：A look at the day ahead in U.S. and global markets by markets correspondent Naomi Rovnick】

item.title: Kantar 称苹果成为首个价值 1 万亿美元的全球品牌
item.description: Kantar's BrandZ 周三公布的全球品牌价值排名显示，美国科技公司苹果成为首个品牌价值突破 1 万亿美元的品牌，比去年增长了 15%。【原文：U.S. technology firm Apple has become the first brand to cross $1 trillion in brand value, a 15% jump from last year, a global ranking by Kantar's BrandZ showed on Wednesday.】

item.title: 中国政府取消关税后，澳大利亚葡萄酒对华出口激增
item.description: 澳大利亚贸易部长周三表示，在中国政府取消关税后的一个月内，澳大利亚葡萄酒制造商向中国运送了价值8600万澳元（约合5700万美元）的葡萄酒。【原文：Australian wine makers shipped wine worth A$86 million ($57 million) to China in the month after Beijing lifted tariffs and should be confident of bumper sales going forward, the trade minister said on Wednesday.】

item.title: 欧盟即将对电动汽车征收关税，中国准备捍卫利益
item.description: 中国外交部周三表示，在一家报纸报道欧盟委员会将对进口中国电动汽车（EV）征收高达 25% 的关税后，中国将采取一切必要措施 "坚决维护 "其合法权益。【原文：China will take all necessary measures to "firmly safeguard" its lawful rights and interests after a newspaper reported that the European Commission would impose tariffs of up to 25% on imported Chinese electric vehicles (EVs), its foreign ministry said on Wednesday.】

item.title: 新加坡第一大银行星展银行高层表示，到 2026 年财富资产将达到 3,700 亿美元
item.description: 星展集团财富业务负责人表示，星展集团计划到2026年底将其财富业务管理的资产规模提高到5,000亿新元（约合3697亿美元），这家新加坡顶级银行押宝新加坡的强劲资金流入。【原文：DBS Group plans to boost assets under management for its wealth business to S$500 billion ($369.7 billion) by the end of 2026, said the unit's head, as the top Singaporean bank bets on robust inflows into the city state.】

item.title: 欧洲央行称欧元的储备货币地位下降，美元和日元的地位受到削弱
item.description: 欧洲中央银行（European Central Bank）的一份最新报告显示，去年欧元在外汇持有量中所占的份额大幅下降，而美元和日元的份额则有所下降。【原文：The share of the euro in foreign exchange holdings tumbled last year at the expense of the dollar and the yen, and further drops are possible whenever Russia becomes free to reduce its own euro stockpile, a fresh report from the European Central Bank showed.】

item.title: 独家报道：资本集团调整战略，力争在 2031 年达到 4 万亿美元的规模
item.description: 资本集团首席执行官迈克-吉特林（Mike Gitlin）告诉路透社记者，该集团的目标是发展固定收益业务，加快海外扩张，并从核心股票业务向多元化发展，以阻止客户撤资，并与增长更快的基金竞争对手展开竞争。【原文：Capital Group aims to grow its fixed income business, accelerate overseas expansion and diversify away from its core equities franchise to stem client withdrawals and compete with faster-growing fund rivals, its CEO Mike Gitlin told Reuters.】

item.title: 瑞银的市场实力令瑞士业界惶恐不安
item.description: 瑞银集团对瑞士信贷的收购，使瑞士企业逐渐产生了一种焦虑，即瑞士企业将为收购后银行的超强市场实力付出代价。【原文：UBS's takeover of Credit Suisse has fed a creeping anxiety that Swiss companies will pay a price for the enlarged bank's outsize market strength.】

item.title: 英国《金融时报》报道：欧盟将对中国电动汽车征收最高 25% 的关税
item.description: 英国《金融时报》援引知情人士的话报道称，欧盟委员会将于周三通知汽车制造商，从下月起对进口的中国电动汽车暂时征收最高 25% 的额外关税。【原文：The European Commission will notify car makers on Wednesday that it will provisionally apply additional duties of up to 25% on imported Chinese electric vehicles from next month, the Financial Times reported, citing people familiar with the matter.】

item.title: 早间竞标美国双人票
item.description: Tom Westbrook 展望欧洲和全球市场的未来一天【原文：A look at the day ahead in European and global markets from Tom Westbrook】

item.title: 中国物价数据疲软，亚洲股市低迷；美国通胀数据即将出炉
item.description: 周三，亚洲股市低迷，因为有数据显示中国的消费价格依然疲软，而美元则在关键的美国通胀报告和将确定近期利率走向的美联储政策决定出台前保持坚挺。【原文：Asian shares were subdued on Wednesday after data showed China's consumer prices still remained soft, while the dollar held firm ahead of a key U.S. inflation report and Federal Reserve policy decision that would set the near-term course for interest rates.】

item.title: 中国消费通胀率稳步上升，工厂通缩收窄
item.description: 5 月份，中国的消费者通胀率稳步上升，而生产者价格下降幅度略有收窄，这进一步表明政府支撑经济的努力已初见成效。【原文：China's consumer inflation measure rose at a steady pace in May while producer price declines narrowed slightly, adding to signs that government efforts to prop up the economy were starting to bear fruit.】

item.title: 新西兰下令调查银行业竞争问题
item.description: 新西兰财政部长尼古拉-威利斯（Nicola Willis）周三表示，新西兰将开展一项调查，评估该国银行业的竞争情况，重点关注农村地区的服务。【原文：New Zealand will conduct an inquiry to assess competition in the country's banking sector, focusing on services in rural regions, Finance Minister Nicola Willis said on Wednesday.】

item.title: 恒大电动车警告资产流失，股价下跌 27
item.description: 中国恒大新能源汽车集团周三股价暴跌 27%，此前该公司表示面临失去土地和设备等关键资产的风险。【原文：Shares of China Evergrande New Energy Vehicle Group plunged 27% on Wednesday after it said it faces the risk of losing key assets such as land and equipment.】

item.title: 消息人士称，美国将扩大对俄罗斯半导体芯片销售的制裁范围
item.description: 熟悉计划的消息人士周二晚些时候称，美国政府计划于周三宣布扩大对向俄罗斯销售半导体芯片和其他商品的制裁，目标是针对中国的第三方销售商。【原文：The U.S. government plans on Wednesday to announce wider sanctions on the sale of semiconductor chips and other goods to Russia, with the goal of targeting third-party sellers in China, sources familiar with the plans said late on Tuesday.】

item.title: 汇市在美国通胀测试和美联储决议前保持稳定
item.description: 美元兑其他货币隔夜触及四周高点后，周三趋于稳定，市场参与者在等待美国的关键通胀数据和美联储当天晚些时候更新的利率预测。【原文：The dollar steadied on Wednesday after hitting a four-week high against peer currencies overnight as market players awaited key U.S. inflation data and the Federal Reserve's updated interest rate projections due later in the day.】

item.title: 数以千计的亚马逊 Flex 司机因被误划为承包商而提出仲裁申请
item.description: 数以千计的亚马逊 Flex 司机代表律师周二向路透社提交了仲裁申请，称他们被误划为独立承包商而非雇员。【原文：Thousands of Amazon.com Flex drivers filed arbitration claims on Tuesday, alleging they were misclassified as independent contractors rather than employees, the lawyer representing the drivers told Reuters.】

item.title: 油价因乐观的需求前景而上扬
item.description: 由于美国能源信息署和欧佩克（OPEC）对全球需求的乐观看法，周三油价走高。【原文：Oil prices ticked higher on Wednesday on upbeat global demand views from the U.S. Energy Information Administration and OPEC.】

item.title: 日本 5 月批发通胀率跳升，令日本央行加息路径复杂化
item.description: 周三的数据显示，日本 5 月份的批发通胀率以 9 个月来最快的年增长率跃升，这表明日元疲软推高了原材料进口成本，从而增加了价格上涨的压力。【原文：Japan's wholesale inflation jumped in May at the fastest annual pace in nine months, data showed on Wednesday, a sign the weak yen was adding upward pressure on prices by pushing up the cost of raw material imports.】

item.title: 特斯拉股东起诉马斯克，要求返还数十亿美元非法所得
item.description: 一名机构股东在周二提起的诉讼中指控埃隆-马斯克利用内幕消息出售特斯拉股票，赚取了数十亿美元，要求法院指令特斯拉首席执行官归还 "非法利润"。【原文：Elon Musk made billions of dollars by selling Tesla stock using insider information, an institutional shareholder accused in a lawsuit filed on Tuesday, asking the court to direct the Tesla CEO to return "unlawful profits."】

item.title: 尽管金价接近历史最高水平，但淘金热仍笼罩亚洲
item.description: 业内官员表示，尽管黄金价格徘徊在5月份创下的历史高点附近，但亚洲对黄金的需求仍在激增，因为买家抢购黄金来对冲地缘政治和经济的不确定性。【原文：Demand for gold in Asia is surging despite prices hovering near the record highs it hit in May, industry officials say, as buyers snap up the metal to hedge against geopolitical and economic uncertainty.】

item.title: 在 "咆哮的凯蒂猫 "引发的零售交易狂潮中，GameStop 募集 21.4 亿美元资金
item.description: GameStop 周二表示，该公司已完成 "场内 "股票发行，募集资金总额约为 21.4 亿美元，此前几天，meme 股票影响者基思-吉尔（Keith Gill）进行了三年来的首次现场直播。【原文：GameStop said on Tuesday it had completed an "at-the-market" equity offering of its shares to raise roughly $2.14 billion in gross proceeds, days after meme stock influencer Keith Gill's first livestream in three years.】

item.title: 亿万富翁投资者 Ryan Cohen 击败 Bed Bath & Beyond 股东诉讼案
item.description: 本周二，亿万富翁激进投资者 Ryan Cohen 赢得了一项股东诉讼的撤诉，该诉讼指控他在 Bed Bath & Beyond 家居用品零售商濒临破产时，过快地从该公司股票中套现获利。【原文：The billionaire activist investor Ryan Cohen won the dismissal on Tuesday of a shareholder lawsuit accusing him of profitably cashing out of Bed Bath & Beyond shares too quickly as the home goods retailer was hurtling toward bankruptcy.】

item.title: 早间竞价：中国 CPI 先于美国 CPI 公布，美联储双重打击
item.description: 亚洲市场前瞻【原文：A look at the day ahead in Asian markets.】

item.title: 谷歌将在巴西测试手机防盗人工智能功能
item.description: Alphabet 旗下的谷歌公司周二表示，巴西将成为首个测试安卓手机防盗功能的国家，该功能可利用人工智能（AI）识别手机是否被盗并锁定设备屏幕。【原文：Alphabet's Google said on Tuesday that Brazil will be the first country to test an anti-theft feature for Android phones that uses artificial intelligence (AI) to identify when a phone has been stolen and lock the device's screen.】

item.title: Theranos 创始人伊丽莎白-霍尔姆斯寻求推翻欺诈定罪
item.description: Theranos 创始人伊丽莎白-霍姆斯（Elizabeth Holmes）和公司总裁拉梅什-"桑尼"-巴尔瓦尼（Ramesh "Sunny "Balwani）的律师周二敦促联邦上诉法院推翻对他们的定罪，因为他们在这家失败的血液检测初创公司中欺诈投资者，这家公司的估值曾高达 90 亿美元。【原文：Lawyers for Theranos founder Elizabeth Holmes and company President Ramesh "Sunny" Balwani on Tuesday urged a federal appeals court to overturn their convictions for defrauding investors in the failed blood testing startup, which was once valued at $9 billion.】

item.title: 埃森哲任命内部人士 Angie Park 为新任首席财务官
item.description: 埃森哲周二表示，目前领导企业与商业金融部门的 Angie Park 将于 12 月 1 日接替 KC McClure 担任公司首席财务官。【原文：Accenture said on Tuesday that Angie Park, currently leading its Business and Commercial Finance division, will take on the role of the company's CFO on Dec. 1, replacing KC McClure.】

item.title: 苹果公司如何利用谷歌的帮助训练人工智能模型
item.description: 本周一，苹果公司首席执行官蒂姆-库克（Tim Cook）在台上宣布与 OpenAI 达成了一项引人注目的协议，将其强大的人工智能模型作为语音助手 Siri 的一部分。【原文：On stage on Monday CEO Tim Cook's Apple announced a splashy deal with OpenAI to include its powerful artificial intelligence model as a part of its voice assistant, Siri.】
